<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/media/chat.css | Updates “see more” masking/height behavior and tweaks request-row styling. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatListRenderer.ts | Detects adjacent waiting confirmations and batches them via placeholders/hidden parts. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatContentParts/toolInvocationParts/media/chatBatchedToolConfirmation.css | Adds styling for the new batched confirmation widget. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatContentParts/toolInvocationParts/chatToolInvocationPart.ts | Adds batching hooks to tool invocation parts (owning/hosting batched confirmation UI). |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatContentParts/toolInvocationParts/chatBatchedToolConfirmationPart.ts | New UI part implementing batched confirmation list with bulk/per-row actions and “pin-to-bottom” behavior. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatContentParts/media/chatSubagentContent.css | Ensures codicon layout in subagent batched confirmations. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatContentParts/chatSubagentContentPart.ts | Batches confirmations inside subagent tool grouping and keeps the batch DOM positioned. |
</details>



<details>
<summary>Comments suppressed due to low confidence (2)</summary>

**src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/chatContentParts/toolInvocationParts/chatBatchedToolConfirmationPart.ts:120**
* The MutationObserver setup here is likely never established for the initial batch: `ChatBatchedToolConfirmationPart` is constructed before its `domNode` is appended to a parent, so `parentElement` is null and `setupObserver` isn’t called. Since `addToolInvocation()` is also called from the constructor (before attachment), `moveToEndOfParent()` returns early and the observer still won’t be set, so the batch may not stay pinned to the bottom when later siblings are added. Consider deferring observer initialization until the node is attached (e.g. retry/schedule until `parentElement` exists, or accept/receive the parent element explicitly).
```
